summary: A PSA from the Community Health Referral Office received a consult designated for the Adult Day Health Care Office. The document was faxed to prefix 615 instead of 617. The patient's consult was faxed to a radio station. The representative from the radio station contacted the VA and informed of the received fax and stated it would be destroyed immediately. The PSA contacted the Radio station again that afternoon and confirmed it was destroyed. The fax had name, home address, social security number and date of birth.

victim.victim_id: United States Department of Veterans Affairs
